{
  "stem": "2718.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So everyone, everybody wanted to get out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Just to reflect back for a minute to when I left it off as far as the going to-- getting food, first there were-- the first few days they called volunteers to get the food for everybody in the barrack.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But afterwards, they didn't call for this because nobody wanted to go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because what it-- what it consisted of, going for food, we had big tumblers, and which had two, two [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] hooks on.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the two hooks with, with-- through the two hooks we put through a long stick, a very strong stick, and one on each end was carrying that, that big pot.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It's about that high.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was very heavy and the soup was very hot, or the food was very hot.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was always, always soft food-- always soup or some sort of a mash.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We called it in Birkenau, we called it [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] was everything was in it but the, the kitchen sink.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "When we got-- when we got to the-- to the kitchen, the reason why we wanted to go to the kitchen is because, I said before, there's always some, some rumors and some news came through about, about families, about who was seen, who was-- who had an unfortunate fate.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Whatever it was, one could hear something else beside the, the regular daily misery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But what we didn't know when we went for food that Jewish kapos took delight in, in beating our legs while we were carrying the, the hot soups and the hot, hot [NON-ENGLISH] so that anybody who didn't lift his legs exactly as they wanted, they had a fantastic time-- Jewish kapos.",
      "word_count": 52
    }
  ],
